etymology:
From Proto-Turkic *til- (“to split, cut in slices”).
Cognate with Karakhanid [script needed] (til-, “to slice”), Old Uyghur [script needed] (til-, “to slice”), Bashkir телеү (telew, “to slice”), Kyrgyz тилүү (tilüü, “to slice”), Turkmen dilmek (“to cut, slice”), Uzbek tilmoq (“to slice”).
